Olunga is currently attached to Japan's top-flight club Kashiwa Reysol but was last week linked with a move to Qatari champions Al Duhail SCMedia reports in Qatar indicated Reysol had accepted an offer worth Sh806 million from Al Duhail in exchange for the former Gor Mahia and Tusker strikerOliech, 35, enjoyed a successful stint in that country, with top tier side Al Arabi, between 2003 and 2005 before moving to France Former Harambee Stars striker Dennis Oliech argues it's time Michael Olunga made some good money from football and should wholeheartedly embrace the move to Qatar if a deal materialises. 

Olunga is currently attached to Japan's top-flight club Kashiwa Reysol but was last week linked with a move to Qatari champions Al Duhail SC. 



