Media reports in Qatar indicated Reysol had accepted an offer worth Sh806 million from Al Duhail in exchange for the former Gor Mahia and Tusker striker. 

All that now remains is for the Upper Hill High School old boy to negotiate personal terms. 

He is said to have asked for a 100 per cent increase to his Sh85 million annual salary at Reysol. 






Kashiwa Reysol forward Michael Olunga jumps as he scores a goal during their J-League match against Kawasaki Frontale at Sankyo Frontier stadium in Kashiwa on December 19, 2020.
Photo credit: Philip Fong | AFP

 

“I haven’t talked to him (Olunga) but heard he has another good offer from Qatar. I encourage him to pick up these offers because he is (almost) 27 and not 22. He has about four or five years remaining at the top level. It is time for him to make good money,” said Oliech, in an exclusive interview. 



