Oliech however warns Olunga that it is not all rosy in the Gulf. 

“He will have to get a strong agent and negotiate a good contract. When I was there, most club owners would delay the salary of  a player when his performance dipped. There wasn’t much of world class management. 

“It is also very hot over there and he will have to adapt fast.” 

Oliech would know a lot about conditions in Qatar. 

Considered one of the greatest Kenyan strikers to put on a Harambee Stars jersey, Oliech, 35, enjoyed a successful stint in that country, with top tier side Al Arabi, between 2003 and 2005 before moving to France. 



